    "Subsequently, another aspect that can make the model predictions inaccurate is label bias [92].",
    "It occurs when the labels assigned to data instances are biased in some way.",
    "For example, a dataset of movie reviews may have been labeled by individuals with a particular preference for a certain genre, leading to biased labels for movies of other genres.Besides them, Aggregation bias refers to a type of bias that arises when a model is used to make predictions or decisions for groups of individuals with different characteristics or from different populations [113].",
    "It occurs when a single model is used to generalize across different groups or subpopulations and can lead to sub-optimal performance for some groups.",
    "For example, scholars study blood glucose (sugar) levels such as HbA1c (widely used to diagnose and monitor diabetes), which usually differ across ethnicities and genders."
  ],
